'''John Byrne''' (born [[June 6]], [[1950s#1950|1950]]) is a comic-book creator who drew a cover for [[Marvel Comics|Marvel's]] [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']] series.

Byrne's earliest professional work was in [[1975]] for [[Wikipedia:Charlton Comics|Charlton Comics]], but he soon found regular work at Marvel Comics and in [[1977]] began pencilling [[Wikipedia:Uncanny X-Men|''Uncanny X-Men'']], which became a runaway success for Marvel. His other notable works include writing and illustrating the [[Wikipedia:Fantastic Four|''Fantastic Four'']] and revamping [[Wikipedia:DC Comics|DC Comics]]' flagship title [[Wikipedia:Superman|''Superman'']] during the 1980s. In the 1990s Byrne went to [[Dark Horse Comics]] to produce his creator-owned title [[Wikipedia:Next Men|''Next Men'']].{{Mediacat|imagecat=Images by John Byrne}}

